    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-21T19:28:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-21T19:28:00-05:00" n="556"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/12–1951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d556fn1">Drafted by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WJA1"
                            >Waldo</persName>; cleared with <gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>;
                        repeated for information to Tel Aviv, Amman, Damascus, Beirut, and
                        Cairo.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-21T19:28:00-05:00"
                            >December 21, 1951—7:28 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3635. Dept increasingly concerned over recent reports from Tel Aviv of incidents
                    on Syrian-Israel and Jordan-Israel borders, continuing failure Syrian-Israel
                        <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> to meet (Gadel 512)<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d556fn2">The same as telegram 246 to Damascus, December 19, <ref
                            target="#pg_968">p. 968</ref>.</note> and deteriorating relations in
                    Jordan-Israel <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>. This latter connection
                    suggest you inform <persName corresp="#p_RWE1">Riley</persName> re Tel Aviv
                        <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 599 Dec 19.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d556fn3">Not printed; it summarized a report in the <hi
                            rend="italic">Jerusalem Post</hi> of December 19 that the Israeli
                        delegate on the Israel–Jordan Mixed Armistice Commission withdrew from the
                        Commission’s December 18 meeting in order to prevent a vote on a change of
                        the border line in the Qalqiliya area which would have transferred to
                        Jordan’s control 100 dunams of Israeli territory (684A.85/12–1951).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Dept interested <persName corresp="#p_RWE1">Riley</persName>’s comments recent
                    reports from Tel Aviv and hopes he will give consideration returning Palestine
                    soonest when his services no longer required Paris. <gloss target="#t_FYI1"
                        >FYI</gloss> since US position re Pal question does not foresee <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWE1">Riley</persName> appointment as Agent Gen and improbable
                    near future <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> will be called on consider Huleh
                    problem, wld appear nothing prevents <persName corresp="#p_RWE1"
                        >Riley</persName>’s early return to deal with deteriorating Armistice
                    sitn.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
